  "texts": [
    "The study investigates the effectiveness of various techniques, such as fine-tuning pre-trained language models for sentiment analysis in the oil market, zero-shot prompt engineering and few-shot prompt engineering, which gives answer to the models with limited labeled examples, proving to be more efficient than traditional sentiment analysis methods.Furthermore, the research explores the use of adapters, small modules incorporated into existing models, to further adapt it to new data without the need for extensive retraining.",
    "The performance of these models is rigorously evaluated, considering factors like accuracy and efficiency, with the ultimate goal of contributing to the development of more effective tools for economic analysis and understanding of the oil markets.",
    "Unfortanutaly such adapters do not have enough gains to be considered worth it for smaller organizations and environmentaly concious organizations.The litterature review, chapter 2, describes the historical progression of deep learning techniques within the field of Natural Language Processing (NLP) [42], emphasizing targeted training methods for domain-specific applications.",
    "Analyzing the evolution from early transformers to masked language models(MLM) [65] and large language models(LLMs) [21,37], examining the computational challenges and opportunities associated with each.",
    "It also provides a comprehensive review of training techniques, including pre-training, fine-tuning, prompt engineering, and few-shot learning, highlighting their significance in developing domain-specific language models [52,15,9,3,13].The next chapter outlines the methodology employed in the research, detailing the datasets and techniques used."
